{"title": "Israel Defence Minister says \u201860 per cent\u2019 of Hamas dead or wounded", "tags": "world", "timestamp": "2024-07-10", "content": "JERUSALEM - Israel\u2019s Defence Minister Yoav Gallant said on July 10 that 60 per cent of Hamas fighters had been \u201celiminated or wounded\u201d in the Gaza war since the militant group\u2019s Oct 7 attacks.\nIn a statement to Parliament on the first nine months of the conflict, Mr Gallant said that the military was \u201cdetermined\u201d to meet its goals of eradicating Hamas and bringing all hostages back from Gaza.\nThe minister praised Israeli soldiers for \u201cperforming their work with dedication, sacrifice and success\u201d and said \u201cthe achievements are many\u201d.\nIsrael has launched major new offensives in Gaza City in the north and around Rafah and Khan Younis in the south, even as it embarks on contacts with international mediators on conditions for negotiating a truce with Hamas.\n\u201cWe have eliminated or wounded 60 per cent of the Hamas terrorists\u201d and \u201cdismantled\u201d most of the Palestinian group\u2019s 24 battalions, Mr Gallant said.\nThe minister did not give figures for the casualties and the Israeli military said it did not immediately have statistics.\nThe Israeli prime minister\u2019s office said on July 10 that \u201c14,000 terrorists have been eliminated\u201d since the beginning of the war.\nIsrael\u2019s army chief, Lieutenant-General Herzi Halevi, told soldiers in central Gaza on July 9 that the Israeli strategy was to \u201capply military pressure in various ways\u201d.\n\u201cIn the end, we go on missions to destroy as much infrastructure as possible, to eliminate as many Hamas operatives as possible, to eliminate as many commanders as possible,\u201d Lt-Gen Halevi said, in a speech shared by the army on Telegram on July 10.\n\u201cIn the end, it reduces Hamas\u2019 capabilities,\u201d he added.\nThe Oct 7 attack on southern Israel resulted in the deaths of 1,195 people, mostly civilians, according to an AFP tally based on Israeli figures.\nThe militants also seized 251 hostages, 116 of whom remain in Gaza, including 42 the military says are dead.\nIsrael\u2019s military retaliation has killed at least 38,295 people in Gaza, also mostly civilians, according to figures from the Hamas-run territory\u2019s Health Ministry.\nWhile many countries expressed solidarity with Israel after the Oct 7 attacks, the government has since faced a wave of criticism for its handling of the war, which has devastated Gaza.\nMr Gallant insisted Israel would stick to its aims.\n\u201cWe have returned half of the hostages and we are determined to return the rest,\u201d he said.\n\u201cThe security establishment, and myself heading it, are determined to achieve the goals of the war and complete them.\u201d AFP"}